que ſyllogiſmus ſaepe numero concludit neceſſitate materiae, ubi forma non eſt bona, Aquila non capit muſcas. And as for the Doctors Syllogiſme (or whoſe ever elſe they are) they differ very much from Mr Powells,
for they are meere negatives (to was not his) Secondly, if they could be found as they are layd downe in any figure, yet they are not in the firſt figure as his was: and therefore the Doctor (or his Amanuenſis) ſhould leave off blinding the people with their captious, vitious, fallacious arguing; and receive the Syllogiſmes more truly and properly retorted upon themſelves, thus;
